<headline>Special Weather Statement issued January 01 at 3:20PM EST  by NWS Boston</headline>
<description>...AREAS OF FOG TO HAMPER TRAVEL THROUGH TONIGHT...
As of 315 PM Saturday...areas of fog still continued across
interior portions of Massachusetts, Connecticut and northern Rhode
Island where visibilities have ranged between one-half and two
statute miles. Fog was also beginning to re-develop across
portions of southeastern Massachusetts as well.
Expect fog to re-develop across most of Southern New England
tonight, with lowering visibilities. Reduced visibilities will
make for difficult travel tonight. A Dense Fog Advisory may be
needed if visibilities of one- quarter mile or less are expected
across a large area.
Motorists are advised to use low-beam headlights and drive at
reduced speeds where visibility is significantly reduced.</description>
